<HEADLINE> Japan Provides Loan for Development Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Japan will provide an amount
of 558.8 million US dollars under a yen loan package to Pakistan
under an agreement signed here today between the two governments.
</P>
<P>
The amount was granted as a soft loan at an interest rate of
2.3 percent repayable in 30 years with a grace period of 10 years.
</P>
<P>
The package includes four projects -- the Lahore Light Rail
system project, the Ghazi Barotha Hydropower project, the national
drainage program and the project for consolidation and improvement
of Middle-Level education in Baluchistan province.
</P>
<P>
The government of Pakistan has decided to construct a modern
light rail transit system for the Punjab provincial capital of
Lahore to alleviate traffic jams.
</P>
<P>
The project envisages a 13-kilometer-long elevated light rail
system which will cater to the most congested parts of central
Lahore.
</P>
<P>
Ghazi Barotha Hydropower Project will include construction of a
barrage on the River Indus to divert water in a 52-kilometer-long
concrete lined power channel.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
