<HEADLINE> Power Supply to Kabul to be Restored in 10 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Power supply to the Afghan
capital of Kabul would be restored within 10 days, said Radio
Kabul monitored here today.
</P>
<P>
The radio quoted acting Afghan Water and Power Minister
Muhammad Ayub as saying that power supply lines had been laid in
many areas in and around Kabul.
</P>
<P>
However, Ayub admitted that due to the low level of water in
the Kabul and the Logar rivers, the Mahipar dam could not meet the
requirements of all the areas of Kabul city.
</P>
<P>
Water is stored during day time and electricity will be
provided at night firstly for hospitals, radio and television
stations, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
