<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean President Stresses Need To Address </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
said on Sunday that there is need for a more comprehensive policy to
address problems faced by ex-combatants.
</P>
<P>
Addressing thousands of people at a ceremony to
commemorate the Heroes day at the National Heroes Acre here, Mugabe
said because of the multi-faced nature of problems affecting war
veterans, there was need for legislation to redress the situation.
</P>
<P>
''In view of the heroic participation of war veterans in the war
of liberation, it is intended that the level of welfare assistance
granted to them be adjusted accordingly,'' said Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
He said the war veterans were now being offered farming
opportunities within the land resettlement schemes while some of them
had already been resettled.
</P>
<P>
A total 22,304 war veterans had been vetted and entered
in an appropriate register for their names to be gazetted soon,
he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the government would continue to advocate free health
care to war veterans who were unable to pay for their medical
services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
