<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Mogadishu's Renewed Factional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 11 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people died and a
dozen others were wounded in a renewed fighting last night
between the militiamen of Ali Mahdi Mohamed and Hussein Mohamed
Aidid, son of General Mohamed Farah Aidid.
</P>
<P>
According to a radio report monitored here today, the
factional fighting, which took place in Warmahan, a village 80 km
west of the Somali capital, was the first since the death of
Somalia's late warlord Aidid on August 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers loyal to Ali Mahdi, the northern Mogadishu
warlord, has cut off a strategic road out of the capital and
seized an anti-aircraft machine gun from Hussein's soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, sporadic shooting also renewed in Mogadishu's
Medina neighborhood this morning.
</P>
<P>
Mahdi's radio accused Hussein's men for attacking his
position. There was no response from Hussein yet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
