<HEADLINE> Bahrain Confirms Resolution of Conflict With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Bahraini Council of
Ministers has confirmed the resolution of the Bahraini-Qatari
conflict within the context of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC).
</P>
<P>
In its regular weekly meeting in Manama today, the Council
pointed out that the settlement of differences between the two
states within the context of the GCC conforms to the traditions
of the Gulf states and peoples, and will be in the best interest
of security, stability, progress and prosperity of the region.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain and Qatar disputed about the sovereignty over a number
of islands in the Gulf. Qatar had taken the case to the
International Court of Justice in the Hague for arbitration.
