<HEADLINE> Air France Cancels Flights to Nice Hit by Strikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Air France today cancled 19
flights from and to the southern resort city of Nice while its
airport runway personnel in the airport of Nice Cote d'Azur staged
a 24-hour strike today.
</P>
<P>
All flights from and to Nice stopped from 10:00 this morning,
after some 250 runway personnel and the company failed to solve a
dispute over salary raise, according to local media reports.
</P>
<P>
However, the Working Force representative said that the workers
signed a new contract all the same this morning with a
representative of the general management of Air France.
</P>
<P>
Some 30 workers blocked the take-off of aircrafts for half an
hour at the tarmac of Nice airport and picketed non-striking
workers from picking up the baggages.
</P>
<P>
The cancellation of the flights represented about 6.5 percent
of the air traffic in the airport of Nice, which registers 150
flights each day and receives 30,000 passengers at the peak of the
vacation season.
</P>
<P>
Air France chartered a TGV bullet train in Paris to send its
passengers to Nice, while a rescue team was put into work at the
Nice airport to take care of aircrafts of other companies.
</P>
</TEXT>
