<HEADLINE> Fatah Central Committee Winds up Meeting in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the PLO's
mainstream Fatah faction wound up here today its two-day meeting,
which mainly discussed means of facing up to Israeli measures that
Palestinians regard as obstacles to the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, who met with Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak Saturday, presided over the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting dealt with Israel's decision to lift a ban on the
expansion of Jewish settlements in the Palestinian territories of
the Gaza Strip and West Bank, a move which Arafat has condemned as
a violation of the agreements already signed between the
Palestinians and Israel.
</P>
<P>
Nabil Shaath, a committee member, said that Palestinians, all
Arabs and the whole world must convince Israel to drop policies
that constitute obstacles to the peace process.
</P>
<P>
According to sources close to the meeting, the committee
drafted a plan to confront these policies. But no details were
available about the draft plan to be ratified at the next meeting
of the committee.
</P>
<P>
The committee members also discussed domestic issues of the
Palestinian self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting is held in Cairo to enable some committee
members who live outside the Palestinian self-rule areas to
attend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
