<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Soviet Debts Bears Heavily on Russia's Foreign Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Russia's foreign debt rose to
120.4 billion U.S. dollars at the end of 1995, 86 percent of which
was inherited from the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
But the number is still well below the 129 billion limit agreed
by the State Duma (Russia's lower house of parliament) in its
debate on the 1995 budget, local press quoted the Finance Ministry
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia has borrowed 17.4 billion dollars since the collapse of
the Soviet Union in September, 1991, four fifths of which, or 14
billion, has come from the International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
The accrual of interest added 6.4 billion dollars to the
former Soviet Union debts, which were 96.6 billion dollars in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Of the 103-billion-dollar debt inheritance, 42 billion is owed
to members of the Paris Club, an IMF affiliate involving ten
American and European powers, and 16.6 billion is owed to members
of the Council for Mutual Economic Assistance, a now defunct
organization set up to help the development of mainly Soviet Union
economies.
</P>
<P>
In April this year, Russia renegotiated 40 billion dollars of
debt with the Paris Club to lift the burden of repaying its
inherited debt. The debt has been rescheduled over 25 years,
including a grace period of six years in which Russia will not
have to make repayments of principle, only interest.
</P>
<P>
Russia would have owed some eight billion dollars of Soviet
debt to Paris Club creditors this year without rescheduling. It
now owes two billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960812.0032 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali FM's Visit to India Aims to Boost </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Foreign Minister
Prakash Chandra Lohani left here this evening for a three-day
visit to India aimed at promoting bilateral trade and economic
cooperation between the two neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that Lohani will hold talks with his Indian
counterpart I.K. Gujral on such issues as trade and transit,
promotion of Indian investment in Nepal, tourism and civil
aviation.
</P>
<P>
Nepal and India already reached an agreement on trade last
month.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, India would remove existing obstacles to
bilateral trade by allowing Nepali products' free entry into
Indian market and lifting countervailing duties on Nepali exports
to India.
</P>
<P>
India also agreed to abolish the limit to Indian investment in
Nepal and responded positively to Nepal's demand for an additional
transit route to Bangladesh through Indian territory, they said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal's trade with India accounts for nearly one-third of its
total foreign trade valued at some 1.5 billion US dollars per
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
