<HEADLINE> Mugabe Urges Defense Forces to Sharpen Skills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Commander-in-chief of the
Zimbabwe Defense Forces (ZDF), President Robert Mugabe said here
today the defense forces during the current period should
intensify training to enhance their operational efficiency.
</P>
<P>
In his address to mark the Defense Forces Day before a crowd
of about 25,000 people at Harare's Rufaro Stadium, Mugabe said
Zimbabwe should have a highly trained and well equipped army able
to meet any eventuality at short notice.
</P>
<P>
"Our defense and security policies should continue to be
non-aggressive as they are based on the principles of equality,
mutual respect and cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
The president termed as pleasing the rationalization and
reduction of the army from over 50,000 to about 40,000, saying it
is in line with the economic structural adjustment program
launched by the government in 1991. 
