<HEADLINE> Largest US Chain Store Enters Into China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A member store and a shopping
plaza invested by the US-based Wal-Mart Chain Store Corporation
opened here today in Shenzhen, one of China's special economic
zones.
</P>
<P>
This marks the first step of this corporation's China plan,
business people say.
</P>
<P>
Last year the Wal-Mart Corporation was reported to have a total
business volume of 90 billion US dollars, ranking the world's
largest retailer.
</P>
<P>
Named Sam Member Shop, the member store is supposed to only
serve those who have the membership. The first of its kind was
set up in 1983 in the United States.
</P>
<P>
At present the newly opened Sam Member Shop already has more
than 30,000 members.
</P>
<P>
According to the president of Wal-Mart (China) Ltd., 80 percent
of the goods it sales will come from China.
</P>
<P>
"We hope we can establish a close relation with the Chinese
clients as soon as possible, and I personally believe that China
is just the right place for us to enlarge our business," he said.
