<HEADLINE> New Oil Pricing Set in Philippines This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Energy Regulatory
Board announced it is set to implement this week the first round
of increases for the price of gasoline under the new automatic
pricing mechanism, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the new prices for gasoline and the
rest of the oil products will take effect after publication, on
August 12 at the earliest, but no later than August 19.
</P>
<P>
Under the new scheme, the price of gasoline will increase by 50
centavos (2 US cents) per liter, while fuel oil, kerosene and
liquefied petroleum gas are expected to drop by an average of 13
centavos (0.5 US cents) per liter.
</P>
<P>
The move, which is the first step of the comprehensive tax
reform in the country, was initiated due to the huge deficit
brought by the old system which was under the tight control of the
government.  
</P>
