<HEADLINE> Auction on Rare Ancient Books to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- An auction on rare ancient
books, periodicals and journals in different historical periods is
to open here on September 14, 1996.
</P>
<P>
At least 171 ancient rare books, periodicals and journals,
including written materials in Tang Dynasty (618-907) and Song
dynasty (960-1279) will be sold during the auction, according to
Shen Wangshu, general manager of the China Bookstore.
</P>
<P>
A great number of rare modern books and magazines on China
written in Japanese or some western languages, records of Beijing
opera, and valuable photos will also be auctioned.
</P>
<P>
All of the books, periodicals and journals will be on display
at the Duoyunxuan in Shanghai from August 16-18 before they are
auctioned at the China Bookstore in Liulichang Street, Beijing, in
September 11-13. 
