<HEADLINE> National Invention Contest for Youngsters Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Eighth National Invention
Contest and Science Seminar for Youngsters and the First National
Children's Science Fiction Painting Exhibition closed today in
Tianjin, a port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
Thirty inventions, 19 papers and 85 paintings were awarded
first prize. A top prize winner was a painting showing robots
doing household chores.
</P>
<P>
A total of 209 youngsters from around the country attended the
activities with 204 inventions and 140 science papers. And a
total of 617 works of imagination were on display on the painting
show.
</P>
<P>
The activities started on August 8.  
