<HEADLINE> Ministry of State Security Warns Cheating Be Stopped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of State Security
today warned in Beijing that people who are engaged in illegal
activities under the guise of being state security personnel will
be severely punished.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a circular that no organizations or
individuals are permitted to pass themselves off as state security
organizations or personnel; no forgery or illegal use of relevant
seals, documents or special signs is permitted; and those who are
engaged in these illegal activities must stop and turn themselves
in.
</P>
<P>
The ministry called on government departments at all levels and
people to be cautious.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held here today, the Ministry of State
Security released information about some of the cheating cases.
</P>
<P>
According to a ministry spokesman, the majority of the
incidents occurred in the economic sector. Some imposters violated
the human rights of citizens, spread political rumors and
committed crimes overseas, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Workers in state security departments must carry identification
cards and produce them when they are on the job, he said. 
</P>
