<HEADLINE> Weekly Report on China's Production Materials Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- On China's domestic market of
production materials last week, prices for major materials such as
rolled steel, nonferrous metals, and chemical products kept going
down, while those for coal, timber and building materials remained
stable.
</P>
<P>
According to China Materials Information Center, the average
prices for 42 varieties rose, those for 54 declined, and those for
the rest of 37 remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Of the 39 varities of rolled steel products monitored by the
Center, 13 recorded price rises; 32 witnessed price falls; and
four remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
On the spot market for nonferrous metals, copper was quoted at
an average of 24,284 yuan a ton, down 306 yuan over the previous
week; aluminum was 15,950 yuan a ton, down 172 yuan; and nickel,
82,088 yuan a ton, down 118 yuan.
</P>
<P>
On the chemical materials market, prices for a number of
products such as rubber, plastic materials, organic materials and
inorganic products continued the downward trend in most areas.
</P>
<P>
The domestic automobile market remained sluggish because demand
was restricted by lack of fund in most businesses. For example,
the average price for Jetta sedans manufactured by the No. 1
Automotive Works was quoted at 143,678 yuan a unit, down 2,088
yuan over the previous week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
