<DOCNO> XIE19960812.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Costa Wins San Marino Tennis Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Alberto Costa of Spain beat his
compatriot Felix Mantilla 7-6. 6-3 to win the title of the San
Marino tennis tournament on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Costa, ranked 18th in ATP Tour, overcame a 0-3
first-set deficit and forced a tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
Mantilla once led 7-6 in the tiebreaker, but he missed the set
point while Costa took the chance to win the tiebreaker 9-7.
</P>
<P>
Costa broke Mantilla's serve twice in the second set to win the
match. The final lasted one hour and 37 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The final was orginally scheduled on Sunday. But it could only
been played on Monday as rain forced the postponement.
</P>
<P>
Pablo Albano and Lucas Arnold of Argentina won the doubles
title after beating another Argentine pair of Mariano Hood and
Sabastian Prieto 6-1, 6-3. 
</P>
