<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Myanmar Sign Accord on Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Myanmar today
signed an agreement on economic, scientific and technical
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad and visiting Myanmar
leader Than Shwe witnessed the signing which will pave the way for
both sides to set up a joint commission to look into "spurring
cooperation in various fields."
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference after the signing ceremony,
Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said that
Malaysia is expected to sign several more trade-related agreements
with Myanmar when Mahathir visits that country soon.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir has agreed to visit Myanmar at the invitation of
Chairman of the State Law and Order Restoration Council Than Shwe
who arrived here earlier today for a five-day official visit, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The proposed agreements will be on investment guarantee,
avoidance of double taxation and bilateral payments arrangement,
said the minister, who described the relationship between Malaysia
and Myanmar as "a constructive engagement."
</P>
<P>
The total trade volume between Malaysia and Myanmar had an
almost triple increase in the last four years from 231.6 million
ringgit (about 92.64 million U.S. dollars) in 1991 to 683.5
million ringgit (about 273.4 million dollars) in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia, with a total investment of 227.27 million dollars, is
now the sixth largest investor in Myanmar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
