<HEADLINE> Beijing University's New President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Chen Jiaer has been appointed as
the new president of Beijing University, it was announced at the
university here today.
</P>
<P>
Xu Songtao, Vice-minister of Personnel, named Chen as the State
Council's choice.
</P>
<P>
Chen was born in Shanghai in 1934. He received a degree in
physics in 1954 from the People's University of Northeast China --
the predecessor of the current Jilin University -- and began work
at the Physics Department of Beijing University in 1955. He has
served there as a professor and doctorate tutor since 1984.
</P>
<P>
The new president was elected a member of the Chinese Academy
of Sciences in November, 1993, and began his term as
vice-president of Beijing University in August, 1984. He was named
deputy director of the State Natural Sciences Foundation Committee
in January, 1991.
</P>
<P>
Chen replaced Wu Shuqing, whose tenure has expired. 
</P>
