<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strange Banana Disease Hits Eastern Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A strange banana disease is
spreading in Uganda's banana-rich counties in the eastern Mbale I
District, reported the local newspaper "the Monitor" today.
</P>
<P>
The disease attacks the roots of bananas, turning the leaves
of affected plant yellow, until it is dry and dead in a week or
two.
</P>
<P>
Since the disease was first reported last month, it has
completely destroyed a number of banana gardens. Although local
farmers suspect the disease to a simple weevil infection, there
has been no official identification of the attacker.
</P>
<P>
Bananas serve as a staple food in the east Africa country,
where the production output increased from 7.763 million tons in
1988 to 8.5 million tons of last year, accounting for 20 percent
of the world banana production and ranking first in the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
