<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commentary: Congress Urges Combined Efforts to Protect Earth (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Liu Dongsheng, a Chinese scientist studying the continuing
upward movement of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, said people should
not neglect the new trend of frequent incidences of natural
disasters as a result of a change in the globe.
</P>
<P>
Disaster-reduction is a difficult problem that nature has posed
for all geologists, he said.
</P>
<P>
A group of participants shared the view that no individual
country could independently solve the problems of global warming
and the rising of sea levels.
</P>
<P>
Regional forest destruction has led to global
warming. Pollution and deterioration of the environment in one
country would bring disaster to neighbouring countries.
</P>
<P>
The best solution to worsening environmental conditions is
concerted efforts by scientists in all disciplines and from all
countries, a participant said.
</P>
<P>
To this end, the current congress called on geologists in all
countries to combine the research of changes in the global climate
with that of deterioration of the ecological environment, and the
research of water shortage to that of pollution, in a bid to fight
any disaster and ensure a sustained development.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng proposed, at the opening ceremony of
the congress, an advance in the study of improving the conditions
of people's living and development from a regional scope to a
global dimension.
</P>
<P>
W.S. Fyfe, president of International Union of Geological
Sciences said: "We need new partnerships for the management of the
Earth. For most of the great world problems we require integrated
teams of experts from many of the classical disciplines."
</P>
<P>
Song Ruixiang, chairman of the IGC organizing committee and
China's Minister of Geology and Mineral Resources has stressed,
more than once, the equal importance of mineral prospecting and
environmental protection in the long period to come.
</P>
<P>
It is the common wish of all participants that this geological
gathering would combine the efforts of all countries to protect
the earth and contribute to the world's future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
