<DOCNO> XIE19960812.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gansu's Stable Growth in Industrial Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Macro-economic control and
improvement in the economic climate in northwest China's Gansu
Province has helped the important heavy industry base to witness a
stable growth in industrial production this year.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value at or above the local county level
reached more than 19.7 billion yuan during the first half this
year, a increase of 6.24 percent over the same period in 1995.
</P>
<P>
This year the province exerted greater efforts to make up for
local shortages in electricity, as well as circulating funds for
industrial development, which both imposed a heavy restriction on
local economic development.
</P>
<P>
The province purchased 1.3 billion kwh of electricity from
neighboring provinces and regions to ease electricity problems
this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition to increasing bank savings, the province also
attached more importance to restructuring its credit mix, and to
increase loans for local state-owned enterprises at preferential
conditions.
</P>
<P>
Local remaining bank deposits reached nearly 73 billion yuan by
the end of June this year, a rise of more than 9.6 billion yuan
from the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
During the first half this year, the province added more than
5.5 billion yuan of loans, 1.9 billion yuan of which were granted
as circulating funds, rising 800 million yuan over the same period
in 1995.
</P>
<P>
During the six-month period, the province reaped more than 3.6
billion yuan in revenue, and more than 3.5 billion yuan in pre-tax
profits, both rising more than 25 percent over the same period in
1995.
</P>
<P>
The period also saw the province keep a speedy growth in fixed
assets investment which exceeded 4.7 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
