<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian Government
should spend more time fostering good relations with the Asian
region, former foreign minister and now Deputy Opposition Leader
Gareth Evans said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to a gathering of the Western Australian Chinese
Chamber of Commerce in Perth, a port city in the west, he said, he
was disappointed to see the federal government's lack of attention
to the Asian region.
</P>
<P>
