While "in the present government very few people have spent any
time at all getting to know the larger region in which we live,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Evans stressed the importance of looking after young Asian
students studying in Australia, who can often feel culturally
isolated.
</P>
<P>
He also urged young Australians to think in new ways about
Asia, and travel as much as possible to "set about the realization
of a truly multicultural society".  
