<HEADLINE> China to Let More Able Persons Work in Backward Western Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xi'an, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China is to mobilize more able
people to work in the country's economically underdeveloped
western regions.
</P>
<P>
They will be heading for areas which lack intellectuals or
people with different skills.
</P>
<P>
People of the same trade will be exchanged between the western
and eastern regions, according to Ministry of Personnel officials
who attended a national meeting on talent markets held in Xi'an,
capital city of Shaanxi province in Northwest China.
</P>
<P>
According to the officials, the country will firstly make
efforts to meet the immediate needs for some specialists by the
West, and then, as a second step, a complete personnel exchange
system between the East and West will be formed to tackle the
problem on a long-term.
</P>
<P>
The western regions have suffered a sustained lack of talented
people and a serious brain-drain, owing to its poor natural and
economic conditions.
</P>
<P>
Efficient methods are yet to be found to attract young college
graduates and middle-aged professionals to work in the area.
</P>
</TEXT>
