<HEADLINE> Syrian FM Leaves for Algeria, Morocco </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq
al-Shara left here this morning for a visit to Algeria and Morocco.
</P>
<P>
Shara brought with him a message from Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad to both Algerian President Liamine Zeroual and Moroccan
King Al-Hassan II on the recent developments in the Middle East
and the future of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian foreign minister's current visit to the two
countries comes within the framework of implementing the recent
Cairo Arab so as to boost inter-Arab cooperation and coordinate
the positions of Arab states on the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian minister is expected to brief both President Zeroual
and King Hassan II on the outcome of the recent visit by King
Hussein of Jordan to Damascus, and the consistent attitudes
adopted by both Syria and Lebanon on the "Lebanon first" initiative
worked out by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
The "Lebanon first" initiative proposes an Israeli troop
withdrawal from Israel's self-proclaimed "security zone" in south
Lebanon first to pave way for arrangements to ensure security on
northern borders of the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
Arab states, especially Syria and Lebanon, rejected strongly the
the "Lebanon first" plan, emphasizing that Syrian-Lebanese
coordination should last until an overall and just peace is
achieved in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
