<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Economic Development Strategy Discussed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's overall development
strategy should be formulated on opinions broadly solicited from
Hong Kong people, said members of the Economic Panel today.
</P>
<P>
At the fifth session of the Economic Panel of the Preparatory
Committee of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
that ended its session in Beijing today, principal officials of
the British Hong Kong government were invited to give briefings on
Hong Kong's development strategy. The briefings covered the
demands on land, transportation and environment in the coming 10
years. The panel members held that it is very important for the
region's future development.
</P>
<P>
As Hong Kong will be more closely related to China's inland
areas in its transportation, port and economy in the future, they
said, contacts between the two sides should be increased when
formulating the strategy, to make it fit Hong Kong's future
development.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, government officials from
neighboring Shenzhen also gave a briefing on the project for a
corridor linking the west part of Shenzhen and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the establishment of a mortgage securities firm in
Hong Kong was discussed and relevant suggestions will be submitted
to the Hong Kong Monetary Authority.  
</P>
