<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Trade Gap With India Widens Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The trade gap between Bangladesh
and neighboring India increased by 52.11 percent during the last
fiscal year that ended in June 1996, according to the latest
official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh ran a trade deficit of 1.45 billion U.S. dollars
with India in 1995-96 as against 952.82 million U.S. dollars the
previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh exported goods worth 64.64 million U.S. dollars to
India while it imported 1.51 billion U.S. dollars worth of goods
from India.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh government has proposed tariff rebates on 20
items for easier access to Indian market for Bangladeshi goods and
the Indian side is likely to give a positive response within a
week, reports said.  
</P>
