<HEADLINE> Thailand, Indonesia to Set Up Fishing Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and Indonesian will set
up a joint venture to pave the way for Thai fishing fleets to
trawl in Indonesian waters, according to Plodprasop Surassawadee,
chief of the Thai government's Fisheries Department.
</P>
<P>
Plodprasop was quoted today by the local newspaper Bangkok Post
as saying that he was told by the Indonesian Fishery Department
that Thai fishing fleets are welcome to trawl in Indonesian waters
which are abundant in marine life.
</P>
<P>
"The Thai-Indonesian fishery Co. will be set up in order to
allow Thai fishing vessels to operate in Indonesian waters
legally," he said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's fish marketing organization will be the major
shareholder in the company, and its initial funding will be
provided by the Thai Export and Import Bank.
</P>
<P>
"In the beginning, the department will invite about 20 Thai
trawlers to participate in a fishing trial in Indonesian waters to
ensure that it is a profitable investment," he said.  
</P>
