<HEADLINE> More People in Shanxi Out of Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
By the end of 1985, Shanxi, in the north of China, still had an
impoverished population of more than 4.5 million, living mainly in
50 mountainous counties in Luliang Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
The central and provincial governments invested two billion
yuan in the past decade to help local people fight poverty.
</P>
<P>
The province devoted greater efforts in building irrigation and
drinking water systems, roads, schools, hospitals and
telecommunication facilities.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, farmers have set up rural enterprises, orchards and
livestock farms to achieve an overall economic development.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the per capita income of 1.23 million poor people
has risen to 850 yuan (102.4 US dollars) and per capita
consumption of grain has increased to 300 kg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
