<DOCNO> XIE19960812.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Volcanoes Doomed the Dinosaur: China Conference Told(2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The theory, however, has been challenged by some scientists,
who found traces of extinction even under the iridium earth layer,
which means the dinosaur may have exited even before the large
meteor struck the earth.
</P>
<P>
French Professor Donze Pierre raised his doubts on the theory,
saying: "I don't believe that single event can kill all the
dinosaurs in a sudden".
</P>
<P>
He believed that the dinosaur's physical defects led to its
downfall.
</P>
<P>
"The direction of its evolution was wrong, " he said.
</P>
<P>
The lush plants and plentiful supply of oxygen in the Jurassic
Period (150 million years ago) made the dinosaur evolve towards its
large size. But its large appetite caused a decrease in plants and
oxygen, and finally led to its extinction.
</P>
<P>
Some scientists attribute the extinction to a deadly plague. No
final agreement has ever been reached by the international
paleobiology circle on the reason for dinosaurs to become extinct.
</P>
<P>
"The extinction process is too complicated to be explained by a
single theory, " said Zhao Xijin, research fellow of the Institute
of Vertebrate Paleontology and Paleoanthropology under the Chinese
Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
In fact, the extinction of the dinosaur is not the largest one
in the life history. An earlier extinction which occured in the
Permian (about 220 million years ago) was larger than it, not only
in varieties, but also in numbers of animals and plants coming to
grief.
</P>
<P>
Many international-renowned paleobiologists have now shifted
their research focus from the dinosaur to the Permian Period.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
