<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Marching towards Information Society </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- An information-oriented
society is taking initial shape in the Pearl River Delta Area of
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Computers and information networks have been put into wide use
in the area's Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Foshan, Huizhou and
Dongguan cities, which give priority to electronics industry.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of big-name information equipment
manufacturers such as TCL, Great Wall, Liangxiang and Huayuan,
which are famous for their computer products, have been set up in
the area in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Many overseas electronics giants, including NEC, Epson, IBM,
Compaq and Conner, have settled in the area.
</P>
<P>
Information technology and hi-tech industries in the area
generated up to 52 billion yuan (about six billion US dollars) in
output value last year.
</P>
<P>
The area has already completed the construction of a mobile
phone and digital data network, and turned all its local phone
networks program-controlled.
</P>
<P>
Computers and on-line services are becoming more popular in the
area, since information technology is widely used by most
enterprises and computers have entered ordinary families.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the area has more than 100,000 computers,
about 100 computer networks in operation and 2,240 Internet
subscribers.
</P>
<P>
The Pearl River Delta Area also has about 10,000 information
services with cable TV networks reaching everywhere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
