<HEADLINE> China Boosts Exports of Machinery and Electronics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China plans to export 60 billion
US dollars worth of machinery and electronics in 1998, a recent
meeting on exports has heard in Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
According to Shen Liechu, director of the office in charge of
China's imports and exports of machinery and electronics, China
exported almost 44 billion US dollars worth of machinery and
electronic goods in 1995, up from 1.68 billion US dollars in 1985,
ranking first in the country's exports.
</P>
<P>
Shen attributed the good result to China's technical
transformation, and the increasing demands of the world market for
machinery and electronic goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
