<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Invest More in Seven Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China plans to invest 5,100
billion yuan in seven major industries during the 1996-2000
period, the overseas edition of People's Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Of the investment, 280 billion yuan will be used in
agriculture, 2,000 billion yuan in the energy development
industry, equalling the total amount of investment in the previous
ten years, and 1,134.8 billion yuan in transport.
</P>
<P>
The petrochemical industry will receive a total investment of
460 billion yuan, automobile industry 280 billion yuan, nine times
that of the total investment in the 1988-92 period, electronic
industry 429.3 billion yuan, and machinery industry between 500
and 600 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
