<HEADLINE> University of Medicine, Engineering To Open In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A private university
offering courses in medicine, engineering and management will
open in October in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
The Vignan International Medical and Technological University
(IMTU) will be the fifth largest in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
A senior official from the Indian High Commission in Tanzania
told Xinhua today that a three-men delegation from India is
expected in Tanzania next week to complete formalities for
setting up the IMTU.
</P>
<P>
The Indian official said the university will wholly funded by
the Vignan Educational Foundation (VEF) of Bangalore, India,
which runs professional educational institutions and hospitals.
</P>
<P>
According to the Indian official, a memorandum of
understanding was signed last December between the government of
Tanzania and VEF for the establishment of the institution.
</P>
