<HEADLINE> More Farmers in Jiangsu Drink Clean Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- All farmers in Jiangsu, China's
largest economic province, will be drinking clean water by the end
of the century.
</P>
<P>
The province has built 6,500 water works to supply tapped water
for over 30 million farmers, an increase of 61 percent over 1990.
</P>
<P>
During the 1991-95 period, the province raised 1.78 billion
yuan to build 2,728 water works for 12.21 million people in rural
areas.
</P>
<P>
The provincial authorities have pledged to build or improve
more water facilities to enable all farmers to drink clean and
fresh water by the end of this century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
