<HEADLINE> Zambian Oil Companies Compete With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Six local oil companies have
emerged in Zambia and they are competing with multi-national
companies in marketing petroleum products in the country.
</P>
<P>
"Times of Zambia" today quoted Evaristo Kasunga, chief
executive of the National Oil Company, as saying that since the
sector was liberalized, a total of six new oil marketing companies
wholly owned by Zambians had surfaced.
</P>
<P>
They are participating in the distribution of petroleum
products competing with such multi-nationals as BP Zambia, Caltex
Zambia, Mobil Zambia, Agip Zambia and Total Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive expects more local oil companies to
emerge. Participation of Zambians in the liberalized energy
sector is helping expand the sector, he said. 
