<HEADLINE> Shanghai Half Way to $US 12.5 Billion Export Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has smashed through
the half way mark in its drive to win 12.5 billion US dollars of
exports this year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June the city has notched up 6.5 billion US
dollars of exports.
</P>
<P>
The city will give priority to cooperation between local
industrial enterprises and foreign trade companies, in a bid to
help the enterprises increase their share of overseas markets to
boost the city's exports.
</P>
<P>
A system of cooperation between industrial enterprises and
foreign trade companies has been set up in the local light
industry. The cooperation is expected to be expanded to machinery
and electronics, textile, metallurgical, pharmaceuticals, and
chemical industries in future.
</P>
<P>
The city will place emphasis this year on developing markets in
East Europe, Latin America, Middle East, Africa and Southeast
Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
