<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey, Iran Sign Multi-Billion Dollar Gas Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Turkey signed here today
a 20 billion U.S. dollar gas agreement despite U.S. threat to
impose tough sanctions on Ankara.
</P>
<P>
The multi-billion dollar contract was signed by the two
neighboring countries only one week after U.S. President Bill
Clinton signed the D'Amato bill into a law to punish
non-American companies investing at least 40 million dollars in
oil and gas industries of Iran and Libya.
</P>
<P>
Based on the accord, Iran will export 4-10 billion cubic
meters of gas to Turkey for 22 years beginning from 1999.
</P>
<P>
Iran will build a 260-kilometer long pipeline from the vicinity
of Tabriz, northwestern Iran, to the Turkish border within three
years and a half.
</P>
<P>
Iran would be getting an annual profit of 1 billion
dollars from the gas sales. 
</P>
