<HEADLINE> Lebanon's Exports Grow 26.4 percent in 6 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese exports increased
during the first half of this year by 94 million U.S. dollars,
or 26.4 percent, over the same period last year, the Beirut
Eco News business weekly reported today.
</P>
<P>
The weekly quoted figures released by the Ministry of Finance
as saying that exports in the first six months reached 449 million
dollars, as against 355 million dollars for the same period in
1995, with the monthly average jumping to 75 million dollars in
1996 from 69 million dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Imports also encouragingly dropped during the same period to
3,471 million dollars in 1996 from 3,540 million dollars in
1995, a decline of 38 million dollars, or 6.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the balance of payments deficit for the first
six months of 1996 was 3,022 million dollars while the
corresponding deficit in 1995 was 3,185 million dollars. 
</P>
