<HEADLINE> Yantai Refuses Pollution Generating Foreign Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Coastal city Yantai in Shandong
province has put beauty before business to protect its famous
environment.
</P>
<P>
It has refused the establishment of 16 foreign-funded
projects, Including a plant to generate power by burning imported
waste plastics.
</P>
<P>
To protect the environment, the city's environment protection
departments are entitled to examine and approve all projects, and
to order the closure of enterprises discharging heavy pollutants,
a city official said.
</P>
<P>
A survey found that four paper mills were ordered to close down
in the first six months of this year, and dozens of industrial
projects cancelled in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The city government has invested 1.77 billion yuan in building
a number of urban smoke-control districts and waste
water-treatment facilities over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
Yantai's sound investment conditions have attracted more
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The city has 154 foreign-funded projects each with an
investment of more than 10 million US dollars. Eighty percent of
them are new and high-tech. 
</P>
