<HEADLINE> ASEAN Vehicle Parts Makers to Get Special Tax Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 12 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN makers of vehicle parts
will get special tax privileges under the ASEAN Industrial
Cooperation (AICO) scheme as Thailand has agreed to waive a 30
percent local shareholding requirement.
</P>
<P>
But the scheme requires that ASEAN residents must have at least
a combined 30 percent of the shares in a project.
</P>
<P>
AICO projects will attract preferential tariffs of zero to 5
percent in line with the common effective preferential tariff of
the ASEAN Free Trade Area.
</P>
<P>
Investors should be able to show that their project meets one
of the three following criteria: strengthening supporting
industries and ensuring transfer of technology to the host
country; the product having never been made in the host country
before; or the project being based in a remote area to distribute
growth.
</P>
<P>
Thailand and Singapore have made commitments to the new plan,
other ASEAN members -- Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Vietnam -- are expected to do so when ASEAN economic
ministers meet in Indonesia later this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
