<HEADLINE> Joint Efforts to Beat Import of Foreign Trash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Customs, commodity inspection
and environmental protection departments in Shanghai have reached
an agreement to jointly fight the import of foreign trash.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the three sides will give full play to
their respective functions, set up regular channels of
communication and mechanisms of consultation to crack down on
importers of foreign trash.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is one of the key opening ports in China. Over the
past few years, it has witnessed several cases of foreign trash
imported from western countries, including the United States.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is not only seen as a strong measure to curb
foreign trash imports, but will promote coordination between the
departments, officials said. 
