<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Banks Asked to Take Action Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Bank, the central bank
in the country, on Sunday directed all scheduled commercial banks
to take strong measures including legal actions against defaulters
to improve their loan recovery rate.
</P>
<P>
The central bank in a circular directed the board of directors
of the commercial banks to hold a special meeting at least in
every three months to review the recovery situation of their
respective banks.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said that the total amount of bad debt
continued rise in recent years and was too much high against the
total amount of the bank loan. No specific figure was given by
the bank.
</P>
<P>
The bank warned that the high amount of bad loan has created an
adverse impact on the investment situation and the maintenance of
price stability.
</P>
<P>
The central bank also asked the commercial banks to appoint
well-known lawyers on trial basis for conducting cases against top
loan defaulters. 
</P>
