<DATE_TIME> 1996-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Human Smuggling Gang Smashed in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Police in the northern German port
city of Hamburg have unearthed a criminal gang which had smuggled
thousands of foreigners into the country, the biggest of those
that have ever been smashed in Germany.
</P>
<P>
The human smuggling ring includes three groups, each consisting
of 15-20 men, most of whom came from Afghanistan, Lebanon and
Germany, according to Guenter Heerdt, a Hamburg police officer.
</P>
<P>
At present, 11 gang members have been arrested, and 14 others
are now held in custody for further interrogation, the officer
said.
</P>
<P>
In a raid on the gang's 36 strongholds based in Hamburg and
other places, police seized a good many of forged passports, blank
forms, seals as well as criminal tools. It is estimated that all
the forgery have a black market price of about 1 million German
marks (about 664,231 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to initial investigation results, the human traders,
who can make a net profit of 15,000 German marks (about 9,963
dollars) from each foreigner, always promised foreigners a good
life in Germany. If illegal immigrants cannot turn in the money in
time, they are often forced to commit crimes, including document
forging, drugs and arms trafficking as well as human smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The criminal organizations, usually transnational in nature,
involve businessmen, tourism companies and civil servants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
