<HEADLINE> Ukraine Adopts New Measures to Better Higher Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine has taken new measures to
cut back spending and clear back-payments to college teaching and
administration staffs, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The measures include the lay-off of one third of the teachers
in the medical universities or colleges, the reduction of nearly
10,000 students from the planned enrollment and the closure of 12
correspondence and evening schools this year.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Ukraine has also increased enrollment of "contract
students" who attend classes on contracts signed with the
university authorities, and expanded the students body that pays
for its own tuitions and other expenses.
</P>
<P>
These new measures have already produced initial results,
particularly the drop of back-payment to college teaching and
administration staffs from 18.6 trillion rubles to 17.1 trillion
rubles (about 97 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
