<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Bridge Being Built In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The two sections of Shanghai's
new Xupu Bridge have been linked.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is the fifth, as well as the third cable stayed
crossing, over the Huangpu River which separates Pudong New Area
from Shanghai proper.
</P>
<P>
The Xupu bridge is a part of a city ringroad under
construction, and a key link in the Shanghai-Hangzhou and
Shanghai-Nanjing expressways. It will also help connect Hongqiao
International Airport with a future airport in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is 4,020-meter-long and 217-meter-high, and it has
240 cables. With a road width nearing 36 meters, the bridge will have
eight lanes and a designed speed limit of 80 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The Xupu bridge is scheduled to be open to traffic in the first
half of next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
