<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Villagers Around Mt Merapi Ready for Evacuation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Villagers living on the slope of
Mount Merapi, about 1,200 kilometers east of Jakarta, are ready
for evacuation as the volcano's activities were increasing in the
past few days.
</P>
<P>
"The situation is very worrying as the thick clouds emitted by
the crater have multiplied since the middle of the week," Antara
news agency reported today, quoting an official at the seismic
section of the Yogjakarta-based volcano monitoring service.
</P>
<P>
The volcano was reported to have spewed hot clouds and
light-blazing lava for 27 times which blacked the peak of the
mountain.
</P>
<P>
The villagers have been told to make possible preparations for
evacuation in case of emergency, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Mount Merapi, with an elevation of 2,962 meters, is one of the
most imminent active volcanoes in the world.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000 people live in the immediate vicinity of the
volcano, one of the 127 active volcanoes out of 500 catalogued in
the Indonesian archipelago.
</P>
<P>
The official death toll from the volcano's last eruption in
November 1993 was over 60. It also caused major damage to property
at that time.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
