<HEADLINE> Strong Aftershock Jolts Mentawai Islands, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A strong aftershock, measuring
6.2 on the Richter Scale, jolted Mentawai islands, West Sumatra,
at 5:35 a.m. Sunday (2235 GMT Saturday), said reports reaching
here today from Padang, capital of West Sumatra.
</P>
<P>
Sudadi, spokesman for the local meteorology and geophysics
office, said the epicenter was located 120 kilometers off Siberut
island.
</P>
<P>
The tremor was also felt in Padang, about 200 kilometers from
Mentawai island, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, Sunday's aftershocks were much
stronger than the first quake which hit the islands last Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Since Friday up to Sunday, about 50 aftershocks were recorded
by our office. But Sunday's aftershock was the strongest one," he
said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties and losses.
</P>
</TEXT>
