<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles Beats Sanchez Vicario, Wins Canadian Opan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- American Monica Seles claimed
title of the du Maurier Canadian Open for the second consecutive
year by defeating No. 2 Arantxa Sanchez Vicario 6-1, 7-6 (7-2)
Sunday in Montreal.
</P>
<P>
Seles, who shares the world's No. 1 ranking with German Steffi
Graf, went through the tournament without dropping a set at the
packed 10,500-seat du Maurier Stadium.
</P>
<P>
It was the first meeting of the two since Seles beat Sanchez
Vicario in the 1992 U.S. Open final and avenged her only loss to
the Spaniard in the 1992 du Maurier final. Seles holds an 11-1
career record against Sanchez Vicario.
</P>
<P>
Seles won 200,000 U.S. dollars, boosting her career earnings to
dlrs 8.57 million. Sanchez got dlrs 100,000 and passed the dlrs 11
million mark in her 10-year career - the third highest total
behind Martina Navratilova and Graf.
</P>
<P>
Seles, playing with a shoulder injury that might require
surgery after the U.S. Open next month, won her fourth tournament
this year. She has 37 career titles.
</P>
<P>
Seles will keep her co-No. 1 status until February 17 or until
she has played 14 tournaments.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario won the du Maurier in 1994 and shares the
tournament record of four appearances in the final with Chris
Evert and Navratilova. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
