<HEADLINE> Iraq Beats Pakistan 3-0 at Asian Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Iraq downed Pakistan 3-0 Sunday to
set up a showdown with Jordan for the last berth of the Asian Cup
finals.
</P>
<P>
Hussam Fawzi and Radhi Swadi scored a minute apart midway
through the second half Sunday after Saheb Abbas gave Iraq the
lead a minute before halftime, delighting the crowd of over 6,000
at Amman International Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Iraq continued its dominance in the second half and Fawzi got
inside the penalty area to double the lead in the 70th. Swadi
completed the scoring on a 25-meter shot a minute later.
</P>
<P>
Iraq will meet Jordan on Tuesday in the final game of Group
Six, with the winner advancing to the 12-team Asian Cup finals in
the United Arab Emirates December 3-20.
</P>
<P>
South Korea qualified earlier Sunday with a victory over
Vietnam, joining China, Thailand, Indonesia, Iran, Syria,
Uzbekistan, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, defending champion Japan and
host Emirates.
</P>
<P>
A draw on Tuesday would send Jordan to the finals on the basis
of better goal differential. Jordan beat Pakistan 4-0 on Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
