<HEADLINE> At Least Five Drown in Trawler Sinking in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- At least five people drowned and
four disappeared in the sinking of a trawler today off the western
coast of France in a festival organized to collect fund for the
families of victims of sea accidents.
</P>
<P>
Forty-two people have been rescued by the end of the day from
the water two kilometers off the Island of Oleron, but it is still
not known how many people were on the trawler "Essor" when it
sank in the middle of this afternoon, local press reports said.
</P>
<P>
The cause for the wreckage is probably an overloading of
passengers, but a sea surge with waves of two meters high struck
the trawler before it sank. Police have questioned the boss of the
trawler.
</P>
<P>
Many boats came to rescue people fallen from the trawler, who
were participating in the "Festival of the Sea" which is held
each year to help families victimized by sea accidents.
</P>
<P>
Searching is still going on in the night by police with the aid
of helicopters, said local media reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
